You are about to install Seamonkey-portable.

It can be installed on harddrive (ssd) or any removeable drive,
it will survive changes of drive name (usb).

To reinstall or change drive locations just type sminst in
a terminal or go to /usr/local/bin and click on sminst

The first click on Menu->Internet->Seamonkey-portable will ask
you to install and then it will start Seamonkey.  From then on 
clicking Menu->Internet->Seamonkey-portable
will start Seamonkey.

After your first run of Seamonkey you will be asked if you
want to make it your default browser:
smportable_launch "$@"
will be entered in /usr/local/bin/defautbrowser